Based on the briefing before me, 401 relevance is minimal, at best, and outweighed by 403 prejudice. 294, so some of the same questions around the authentication issue so I think that ruling holds. I won't otherwise preclude this evidence. It is potentially corroborative evidence of testimony and 403 prejudice does not rule out 401 but the defense can maintain the search and authentication issues that we have discussed.

Exhibit 403 I won't preclude, it's potentially probative of the relationship between the defendant and Mr. Epstein.
